=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFPulse_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 55 Hz, featuring instant attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 55.1599
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.5442
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8816
  pitch_clarity: 4.8539
  inharmonicity: 0.5253
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.3061
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFPulse Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFPulse.html
// Tags: LFPulse, Classes, oscillator, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
{ LFPulse.ar(XLine.kr(1, 200, 10), 0, 0.2, 0.1) }.play;
